(
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D69B26BFF6EFE12FEC51681" box="[159,308,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1696,1720]" captionTargetBox="[260,1328,181,1672]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[260,1328,181,1672]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Crossomeles acutipennis Chemsak &amp; Noguera, 1993, paratype male. a) Dorsal habitus. b) Close-up of pronotum. c) Close-up of head. d) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577710/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Figures 3a–d</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D69B26BFEB1FE13FE561681" box="[320,423,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,181,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-23@8.[158,1429,181,1720]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Four species of Crossomeles. a) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of head. b) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of head. c) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of head. d) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of head. e) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of pronotum. f) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of pronotum. g) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of pronotum. h) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of pronotum. i) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of metatibia. j) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of metatibia. k) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of metatibia. l) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of metatibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577714" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577714/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">5a, 5e, 5i</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="209E1AAD0D69B26BFF66FE5BFF0114F5" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="683B49260D69B26BFF66FE5BFEBF159E" blockId="5.[151,1437,510,1185]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="5AF095340D69B26BFF66FE5BFE5B1549" bold="true" box="[151,426,510,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Diagnosis and remarks</emphasis>
. This species can be separated from congeners by the elytra longer, extending to near posterior margin of abdominal segment I, narrowly rounded apically; genae about 1/2 as long as lower lobe of eye. In male specimens examined, the eyes are narrowly separated in front by about 7 ommatidia, while in females they are widely separated by more than 20 ommatidia, or about 2/3 width of an eye lobe. Antennomeres VI–XI of both sexes with small, indistinct sensory pores on dorsal and ventral surface of each antennomere (not reported in original description).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="683B49260D69B26BFF36FD72FF0114F5" blockId="5.[151,1437,510,1185]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">
This species was described from a series of 
<specimenCount id="7E8282AF0D69B26BFD4BFD72FCA215A1" box="[698,851,727,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" type="generic">17 specimens</specimenCount>
(
<specimenCount id="7E8282AF0D69B26BFC92FD72FC3A15A1" box="[867,971,727,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" type="male">11 males</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount id="7E8282AF0D69B26BFC26FD72FBA915A2" box="[983,1112,727,754]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" type="female">six females</specimenCount>
) from 
<collectingCountry id="109309B60D69B26BFB57FD72FB0D15A1" box="[1190,1276,727,753]" name="Mexico" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="AA4087C40D69B26BFAFAFD72FAAC15A2" box="[1291,1373,727,754]" country="Mexico" name="Jalisco" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Jalisco</collectingRegion>
). 
<collectingMunicipality id="885FD35C0D69B26BFA80FD72FA6C15A1" box="[1393,1437,727,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">The</collectingMunicipality>
authors mention additional specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="109309B60D69B26BFD7CFD5EFCE31445" box="[653,786,763,789]" name="El Salvador" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">El Salvador</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="109309B60D69B26BFCBDFD5EFC531445" box="[844,930,763,789]" name="Mexico" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="AA4087C40D69B26BFC43FD5EFBFE1446" box="[946,1039,763,790]" country="Mexico" name="Chiapas" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Chiapas</collectingRegion>
) which they considered to be conspecific but differed by having the head, pronotum, and antennae black instead of reddish orange (as in 
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D69B26BFAD3FCBAFA61146A" box="[1314,1424,799,826]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1696,1720]" captionTargetBox="[260,1328,181,1672]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[260,1328,181,1672]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Crossomeles acutipennis Chemsak &amp; Noguera, 1993, paratype male. a) Dorsal habitus. b) Close-up of pronotum. c) Close-up of head. d) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577710/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Fig. 3a–d</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="0C1534D70D69B26BFF66FCE6FE9B140D" author="Swift, I. P. &amp; Bezark, L. G. &amp; Nearns, E. H. &amp; Solis, A. &amp; Hovore, F. T." box="[151,362,835,861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 68" refId="ref4854" refString="Swift, I. P., Bezark, L. G., Nearns, E. H., Solis, A. &amp; Hovore, F. T. (2010) Checklist of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of Costa Rica. Insecta Mundi, 0131, 1 - 68." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Swift 
<emphasis id="5AF095340D69B26BFF2CFCE6FEE6140D" box="[221,279,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
listed this species from 
<collectingCountry id="109309B60D69B26BFD73FCE6FD0C140D" box="[642,765,835,861]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="AA4087C40D69B26BFCFFFCE6FC82140E" box="[782,883,835,862]" country="Costa Rica" name="Alajuela" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Alajuela</collectingRegion>
), but we were unable to examine any specimens from this locality. 
<location id="6D5B1FFD0D69B26BFE93FCC2FE6214D1" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:E02DF8300D69B26BFF66FE37FBEA13F1:6D5B1FFD0D69B26BFE93FCC2FE6214D1" box="[354,403,871,897]" country="Mexico" municipality="The" name="Two" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" stateProvince="Jalisco">Two</location>
female specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="109309B60D69B26BFD54FCC2FD0F14D1" box="[677,766,871,897]" name="Panama" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Panama</collectingCountry>
are listed below, representing a 
<emphasis id="5AF095340D69B26BFB92FCC2FABC14D1" bold="true" box="[1123,1357,871,897]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">new country record</emphasis>
for the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
